# Weather Whether Architecture Rules

## Core concept (align all features)

Grid puzzle where the player **queues a sequence of weather cards**, then watches a pixel-art **character (Sky)** auto-walk from START to GOAL across the transformed board. Six weather cards (Rain, Sun, Frost, Wind, Lightning, Fog) interact deterministically with 14 terrain types. Win = character reaches goal. Lose = character dies on a death tile or no path exists.

**Authoritative spec:** `docs/GAME_DESIGN.md` v2. Always defer to that doc on disputes.

- Mobile-first. Touch is canonical, mouse/keyboard inherit. **Same art/UI assets** on desktop (Steam) and mobile; window framing via `docs/DISPLAY_PROFILE.md`.
- Windows/Steam first release lane.
- Strictly deterministic mechanics. No randomness in puzzle logic.
- Linear unlock per world (Cut the Rope style).
- Sequence model: queue → commit → resolve → walk.
- Pixel art tiles + painterly key art only. Weather feedback: manifest **sprite VFX** first; optional **`GPUParticles2D`** layers are cosmetic only (`docs/GAME_DESIGN.md` §17).
- One-time premium purchase. No IAP, no ads, no live service.

## Visual reference (mocks)

When implementing any UI screen (.tscn / .gd in ui/screens/ or ui/popups/),
first check assets/mocks/ for a layout reference SVG. If a reference exists,
match its proportions in the Godot scene tree. If no reference exists for
the screen you're building, ask the producer to add one before proceeding.

Mock pack contents:
- assets/mocks/level_mockup.svg — full gameplay screen layout (HUD, grid,
  queue strip, hand, PLAY SEQUENCE button) at 360x640 mobile aspect ratio.
  Canonical reference for ui/screens/gameplay.tscn.
- assets/mocks/gameplay_desktop.svg — desktop window chrome placement (logical 1080×1920 with DisplayProfile).
- assets/mocks/tiles.svg — all 14 v2 terrain types with locked colors and
  the colorblind-safe pattern cue per tile.
- assets/mocks/cards.svg — all 6 weather cards with locked per-card colors.
- assets/mocks/character.svg — all 10 Sky character states (idle, walk,
  surprised, cheer, drown, burn, fall, electrocute v1.5, freeze v1.5, hidden).
- assets/mocks/README.md — the contract for what mocks are and are not.

Mocks are SVG layout references, NOT shippable pixel art. The art-pipeline
agent generates real 32-color pixel art per docs/ASSET_PROMPTS_GEMINI.md.
Do not commit the SVG mocks as game assets — they live only in assets/mocks/.
